<subSubSection id="C37FD295FF96FF80306AFF14767C1923" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BDA811EFF96FF80306AFF1476061BAF" blockId="2.[111,648,216,1700]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">
“ 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF803067FF1B77F01E17" box="[124,238,247,273]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF803067FF1B77F01E17" box="[124,238,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Pleurotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF8030E5FF1B765C1E17" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1872" box="[254,322,247,273]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="spiralis">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF8030E5FF1B765C1E17" box="[254,322,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">spiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been consistently attributed to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF8030EEFEFB759C1E34" authority="Harris &amp; Burrows, 1891" authorityName="Harris &amp; Burrows" authorityYear="1891" box="[245,642,279,306]" class="Gastropoda" family="Borsoniidae" genus="Asthenotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF8030EEFEFB76661E37" box="[245,376,279,305]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Asthenotoma</emphasis>
Harris &amp; Burrows, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, in the literature on West African mollusca (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF803068FEBB760A1E74" author="KNUDSEN J." box="[115,276,343,370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" pagination="151 - 157" refId="ref6708" refString="KNUDSEN J. 1952. - Marine Prosobranchs of Tropical West Africa collected by the &quot; Atlantide &quot; Expedition 1945 - 46. Videnskabelige meddelelser fra Dansk Naturhistorisk Forening 114: 151 - 157." type="journal article" year="1952">Knudsen 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF803105FEBB76471E74" author="KNUDSEN J." box="[286,345,343,370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" refId="ref6743" refString="KNUDSEN J. 1956. - Marine Prosobranchs of tropical West Africa (Stenoglossa). Atlantide Report 4: 7 - 110, 4 pls." type="journal volume" year="1956">1956</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF803179FEBB750E1E74" author="COLLIGNON J." box="[354,528,343,370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" pagination="411 - 464" refId="ref6485" refString="COLLIGNON J. 1960. - Observations faunistiques et ecologiques sur les mollusques testaces de la baie de Pointe-Noire (Moyen-Congo). Bulletin de l'Institut francais d'Afrique Noire 22 A (2): 411 - 464." type="journal article" year="1960">Collignon 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF803202FEBB77B41E97" author="BASSINDALE R." pageId="2" pageNumber="7" pagination="481 - 510" refId="ref6439" refString="BASSINDALE R. 1961. - On the marine fauna of Ghana. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 137: 481 - 510." type="journal article" year="1961">Bassindale 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF8030ACFE9A764E1E97" author="BERNARD P. A." box="[183,336,374,401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" refId="ref6465" refString="BERNARD P. A. 1984. - Coquillages du Gabon. La Piramide, Roma, 140 p." type="book" year="1984">Bernard 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF803147FE9A75051E97" author="GOFAS S. &amp; PINTO AFONSO J. A. &amp; BRANDAO M." box="[348,539,374,401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" refId="ref6628" refString="GOFAS S., PINTO AFONSO J. A. &amp; BRANDAO M. [1985] - Conchas e Moluscos de Angola / Coquillages et Mollusques d'Angola. Elf Aquitaine Angola; Universidade Agostinho Neto, Luanda, 144 p." type="book" year="1985">
Gofas 
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF8031BFFE9B76C71E96" box="[420,473,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF80323CFE9A77F41EB7" author="ROLAN E. &amp; RYALL P." pageId="2" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref6861" refString="ROLAN E. &amp; RYALL P. 1999. - Checklist of the Angolan marine molluscs. Resenas Malacologicas 10: 1 - 132." type="journal article" year="1999">Rolán &amp; Ryall 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF8030EDFE7A752B1EB7" author="ARDOVINI R. &amp; COSSIGNANI T." box="[246,565,406,433]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" refId="ref6417" refString="ARDOVINI R. &amp; COSSIGNANI T. 2004. - West African Seashells. L'Informatore Piceno, Ancona, 319 p." type="book" year="2004">Ardovini &amp; Cossignani 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF80325CFE7A77A11ED7" author="GOFAS S." pageId="2" pageNumber="7" pagination="11 - 22" refId="ref6599" refString="GOFAS S. 1990. - Scaevatula n. gen., a sinistral clavatuline Turrid from West Africa. Archiv fur Molluskenkunde 120: 11 - 22." type="journal article" year="1990">Gofas (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF4FCEFFF96FF8030E6FE5A76891ED7" author="GATTO R." box="[253,407,438,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" pagination="37 - 64" refId="ref6557" refString="GATTO R. 1997. - Systematic revision of the Conoidean species of the genus Asthenotoma Harris and Burrows, 1891 from the Italian Neogene. Memorie di Scienze Geologiche 49: 37 - 64, 8 pls, 4 tabs." type="journal article" year="1997">Gatto (1997)</bibRefCitation>
figured 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF8031E1FE5976691EF6" authority="(Mayer, 1868)" baseAuthorityName="Mayer" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Gastropoda" family="Borsoniidae" genus="Asthenotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="meneghinii">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF8031E1FE5977FE1EE9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Asthenotoma meneghinii</emphasis>
(Mayer, 1868)
</taxonomicName>
, a fossil from the European Miocene which is the 
<typeStatus id="54DE3FBCFF96FF803141FE1976961D16" box="[346,392,501,528]" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF8031E0FE19759E1D09" authorityName="Harris &amp; Burrows" authorityYear="1891" box="[507,640,501,527]" class="Gastropoda" family="Borsoniidae" genus="Asthenotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF8031E0FE19759E1D09" box="[507,640,501,527]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Asthenotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species has an evenly biconical shell with the last whorl occupying about two-thirds of the total height, has a distinct axial sculpture forming nodes on the spire and last whorl, and has a simple outer lip with a poorly defined labial notch. The lower part of the columella is quite prominent and borders a large, broadly open siphonal canal. The Recent West African species “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF803102FD1E76921C0A" box="[281,396,754,780]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF803102FD1E76921C0A" box="[281,396,754,780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Pleurotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF803187FD1E76ED1C0A" box="[412,499,754,780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">lamothei</emphasis>
Dautzenberg, 1910 has a quite similar shell architecture although the last whorl is not quite so high, and is possibly a Recent representative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF803195FCBD750D1C6D" authorityName="Harris &amp; Burrows" authorityYear="1891" box="[398,531,849,875]" class="Gastropoda" family="Borsoniidae" genus="Asthenotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF803195FCBD750D1C6D" box="[398,531,849,875]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Asthenotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its radula indicates that it belongs to the toxoglossate 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF803236FC9D75991C8A" authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1822" box="[557,647,881,908]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Conidae</taxonomicName>
but it has a well-developed operculum, which is lacking in “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF8030F6FC5C766C1CCC" authorityName="Harris &amp; Burrows" authorityYear="1891" box="[237,370,944,970]" class="Gastropoda" family="Borsoniidae" genus="Asthenotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF8030F6FC5C766C1CCC" box="[237,370,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Asthenotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF80319FFC5C76D51CCC" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1872" box="[388,459,944,970]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" genus="Pleurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="spiralis">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF80319FFC5C76D51CCC" box="[388,459,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">spiralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This feature and also the general shell architecture are quite different from the species considered hereafter, which have a high spire and relatively low body whorl, completely lack any element of axial macrosculpture, and have a well-defined labial notch. We consider these sufficient reasons to dismiss the current classification as 
<taxonomicName id="4C65FA9DFF96FF803096FB62760C1BAE" authorityName="Harris &amp; Burrows" authorityYear="1891" box="[141,274,1166,1192]" class="Gastropoda" family="Borsoniidae" genus="Asthenotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="7" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9115D0CFF96FF803096FB62760C1BAE" box="[141,274,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="7">Asthenotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
